         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">23/8/91 ¶  ¶ In answer to your letter that has just arrived, ¶ Letter not found. ¶ very esteemed Professor, I would like to mention firstly that for four years quite unusual ¶ extra activities ¶ have ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">91.08.23</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Adolf<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Engler</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Staatsbibliothek zu Berlin, Preussischer Kulturbesitz, Berlin.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">23/8/91.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">In Beantwortung Ihres eben angelangten Schreibens, sehr geehrter Herr Professor, möchte ich zuerst bemerken, dass ganz ungewöhnliche<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Extra-Beschäftigungen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>mich seit 4 Jahren von regelmässigen Arbeiten in der Phytographie abgehalten haben; fürder dass ich<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">zunächst die Bearbeitung der Neu Guinea-Pflanzen des Mr</hi>
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Forbes, welche auf Kosten der geographischen Gesellschaft Australiens gesammelt wurden, vollenden will. Daher ersuche ich Sie, die Bearbeitung der Myoporinae, Dilleniaceae &amp;c für die Pflanzen Familien überstehen zu lassen, bis ich das papuanische Material wissenschaftlich ganz verwerthet habe, zumal da die Vollendung der Pfl. Fam. ja doch ohnehin mehrere Jahre noch in Anspruch nehmen wird. Bei dieser Gelegenheit möchte ich Ihnen nicht verhehlen, dass mich die Geringschätzung meiner eignen Arbeiten von mehreren der Bearbeiter der Pfl. Familien etwas entmuthigt hat, mich selbst an dem Werke direct zu betheiligen. Um nur beispielweise<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">einen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Fall aus neuerster Zeit anzuführen, der zahlreichen früheren nicht zu gedenken, — findet sich auf Seite<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">25</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>der Rubiaceen die Oldenlandia Auricularia verzeichnet, als ob solche neu unter diesem Namen wäre, da doch in dem Census der austral. Pfl von 1882 u 1889 diese Pfl. bereits klar unter dieser Benennung steht. Soviel Sorgfältigkeit oder Gerechtigkeit könnte doch wohl bei der Ausarbeitung eines so grossen u. permanenten Werkes entwickelt werden, dass<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ein Blick</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>wenigstens doch in den Census und auch in die Select plants geworfen würde, um zu sehen, wie weit in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Australien</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>die Forschungen vorgerückt sind. Bei einer Gelegenheit z. B. erschien eine<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Illippe</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>unter einem vermeintlichen neuen Namen, der schon<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">5</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>mal in Werken von mir gedruckt war. Vom Census sowohl als von den Select plants befinden sich mehrere Ex als von mir gesandt in Ihrer Metropolis, als daher leicht erreichbar; u. selbst wäre dies nicht so, dann könnten ja eben diese Werke doch leicht billig u ganz sicher durch den Buchhandel, auf den ich grösstentheils angewiesen bin, bezogen werden. Es ist auch nicht gut, dem Princip zu huldigen, nach welchem Baillon die Autorität für die jüngst auch in Australien gefundene Ourouparia ferrea entzogen wird. Alle solche Benennungen, welche die spätere Wissenschaft ja doch nicht annehmen wird, könnten allerdings ja in der wohl später erscheinenden neuen Ausgabe der Pfl. Fam. berichtigt werden. Ich würde rathen, zuerst den strict<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">phytographischen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Theil (den der Genera) in system. Folge abdrucken zu lassen, denn für bot. Touristen u. Reisende wäre<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">das</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>das Wichtigste; u. für Gebrauch auf Reisen ist das Werk u so ist es mit Baillon's Histoire ja auch nicht<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">annähernd so werthvoll in jetziger Form, u selbst für täglichen Gebrauch der Fachmänner, als B. &amp; H. gen. Sehr erfreulich ist es, dass für die Pfl. Fam. in neuerer Zeit fast nur<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Original</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Bilder</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>geliefert sind, u. eine berühmte Firma, wie die von Engelmann, wird gewiss in der nächsten Ausgabe die vielen geborgten Illustrationen der ersteren Hefte durch eigne Zeichnungen ersetzen lassen. Es hatte sich bei mir der Gedanke gebildet, dass Sie noch immer die Monochlamydeae zusammen halten, was nach Ihrem letzten Briefe mir der Fall ist. So müssen mir Schriften von Ihnen entgangen sein, da ich in den Abhandlungen Ihrer Schüler u Untergebenen noch bis zur neuesten Zeit die Apetaleae schroff von der anderen Abtheilung entfernt zusammen finde. Wäre es Ihnen möglich Ihre<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">neuesten</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Anschauungen in Bezug auf Familien-Sequenz zu veröffentlichen, wie ich es nach meinen 50 jährigen Erfahrungen, namentlich vom australischen Standpunkt, gethan? B. &amp; H. verloren eine glorreiche Gelegenheit, das Juss-D.C System zu verbessern, obwohl ich schon beim Beginn dieser Genera auf die<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Auflösung</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>der Monochlamydeae (1862) drang!</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Selbst von einer einfachen Liste, die aus ihren grossen Erfahrungen und in Ihrer so<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">vortheilhaften</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Stellung hervorgehen möchte, könnten wir Alle ja vergleichend l</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ernen,—</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>obwohl sich bei mir längst die Überzeugung aufgedrängt hat, dass im grossen Ganzen die<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">einzige bedeutende</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Verbesserung des Juss-DC Systems nur in der Vertheilung der Monochlamydeae bestehen kann.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Selbst Central Afrika wird wohl nur wenig liefern, was auf die finale Anordnung der Familien einen bedeutenden Einfluss ausüben kann.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es war mir eine grosse Freude, dass Sie mit Hr Geheimrath Pringsheim u anderen der dortigen höchsten Fachgenossen meine Widmung des neuen Ceratopetalum für das Virchow-Jubelfest in einer so grossmüthigen Weise unterstützten.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Sie ehrend der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Es soll mich wundern, ob der junge Bearbeiter der Salsolaceae seine Ansichten über den Umfang der austral. Arten meinen vieljährigen Erfahrungen u sorgfältigen zusammenhängenden Erwägungen anschliessen wird.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Gewiss wäre es dann auch rathsam, die volksthümlichen Ausdrücke für Pflanzen Organen durch die internationalen ebenso leicht erlernbaren zu ersetzen.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">23/8/91</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">In answer to your letter that has just arrived,</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>very esteemed Professor, I would like to mention firstly that for four years quite unusual<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">extra activities</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have kept me from regular work in phytography; further that to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">begin with</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I intend to complete the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">working up of the New Guinea plants of Mr</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Forbes, which were collected at the expense of the Geographical Society of Australia.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Henry Forbes's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>collecting expedition was supported by British institutions as well as, later, the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Royal Geographical<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Society<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of Australasia, and M was to describe only the dicotyledonous species, the remaining<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>being<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the responsibility of the British Museum (Natural History).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Therefore I ask you to let the working up of the Myoporinae, Dilleniaceae &amp;c for the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Pflanzen Familien</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>stand over</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>until I have completely utili</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">z</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ed the Papuan plants scientifically, especially since the completion of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Pfl. Fam.</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will in any case surely still take several years.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">In M to A. Engler, 20 April 1888 (in this edition as 88-04-20a), M had asked that the Epacrideae and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Myoporinae be reserved for him to write for Engler &amp; Prantl (1887-1915).</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>In this connection I wou</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ld not like to conceal from you</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that the scant regard for my own work by several of the compilers of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Pfl. Familien</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has rather discouraged me from direct participation in the work. For instance</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>only to mention<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>case from most recent times, not to mention numerous earlier</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ones</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, one finds on page 25 of Rubiaceae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Oldenlandia auricularia</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>recorded as if such were new under this name,</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Schuman (1891), p. 25, transfers the species from<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Hedyotis</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Oldenlandia</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>without mentioning that M had previously done so.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Census</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">of Austr. Pl.</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of 1882 and 1889</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B83.03.04,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>B89.12.03.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>this plant already stands clearly under this designation. So much attention or justice could surely be developed in the preparation of so great and permanent a work that there would surely be at least<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">a glance</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Census</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and also in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Select Plants</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to see how far researches in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Australia</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have advanced. In this connection for example, an<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Illippe</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>appeared under a supposed new name which already was published by me<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">five</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>times in publications.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Engler (1890), p. 133; M used<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the name<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Illipe</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in editions of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Select<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">extra-tropical p</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">lants</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>beginning with B84.13.22, p.181, where he transferred<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Bassia latifolia<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Illipe latifolia</seg>.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>There are several copies of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Census</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as well as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Select plants</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sent by me in your metropolis, therefore readily available; and even were it not so, these publications could surely just be obtained easily, cheaply and quite certainly through the book trade, on whom I for the most part am dependent. It is also not good to follow the principle</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">according to which Baillon is deprived of the authority for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Ourouparia ferrea</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Schuman (1891), p.57.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>recently also found in Australia. All such designations, which later science certainly will not accept, could of course be corrected in the edition of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Pfl. Fam.</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">that</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will probably appear later. I would suggest<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">having</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the strictly<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">phytographic</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>part (that of the genera) printed off in systematic order first, because<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">that</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>would be the most important for botanical tourists and travellers; and for use in travelling the work is certainly not nearly as valuable in the present form, even for daily use by specialists, as B. &amp; H.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Gen.</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham &amp;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Hooker (1862-83).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and so it is with Baillon’s<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Histoire</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Baillon (1867-95).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>It is very pleasing that recently almost only<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">original illustrations</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>are produced for the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Pfl. Fam</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">and a well-known firm<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">such<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">as that of Engelmann will certainly have the many borrowed illustrations of the first number replaced by their own drawings in the next edition. I had formed the idea that you will still keep the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Monochla</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">m</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ydeae</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>together, which is the case according to your last letter to me. So letters to me from you must have gone astray, because I find together in the papers of your students and subordinates even recently the Apetalae glaringly distant from the other section. Would it be possible for you to publish your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">latest</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>views with respect to the sequence of famili</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">es, as I did according to my 50-</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">year experiences, particularly from the Australian standpoint? B. &amp; H. lost a glorious oppo</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">rtunity to improve the Juss.-D</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">C</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn9" n="10">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jussieu-De Candolle.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>system, although already by the beginning of their<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Genera</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I urged the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">break</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">-</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">up</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the Monochlamydeae (1862)!</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn10" n="11">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">M to W. Hooker, 29 January 1862</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">(</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">in this edition as 62</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">-</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">01</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">-</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">29a</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">)</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, and M to G. Bentham</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>24 January 1862.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We all certainly learn compar</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">atively even from a simple list</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">that</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>might emerge from your great experience and in your so<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">advantageous</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>position, —</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>although in my case the conviction forced itself upon me long ago that on the whole the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">single significant</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>improvement of the Juss-DC system can consist only in the division of the Monochlamydeae.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Even Central Africa will probably only produce little that can exert a significant influence on the final arrangement of the families.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was greatly pleased that you with Privy Councillor Pringsheim and others of the greatest colle</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">a</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">gues there supported my dedication of the new<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Ceratopetalum</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn11" n="12">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Ceratpetalum virchowii</seg>, named<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in B91.04.01, p. 181,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for Rudolf<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Virchow in celebration of his 70th birthday.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for the Virchow jubilee</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn12" n="13">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to R. Virchow, 4 August 1891<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 91-08-04b).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in such a magnan</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">imous manner.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Respectfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">I should not be surprised if the young contributor of the Salsolaceae</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 12pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn13" n="14">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Georg Volkens.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Volkens (1893)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has at the top of the article the note 'Gedrückt im Februar 1892'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[Printed in February 1892]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and was published as a continuous text in two fascicles, fascicle 70<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(issued<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>March 1892, to which the note about printing seems to apply) and,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>picking up midway through a paragraph, fascicle 79 (issued<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>March 1893): see TL2, publication number 1710.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will incorporate his views about the extent of the Australian species with my many years of experience and thorough coherent deliberations.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Certainly it would also be advisable then to replace the popular expressions for plant organs by the international,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which are just as easily learnt.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dilleniaceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Illippe</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Monochlamydeae<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Myoporinae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Oldenlandia auricularia</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Ourouparia ferrea</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Rubiaceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Salsolaceae</p>
         </div>
